verbs.description: debarrass (third-person singular simple present debarrasses, present participle debarrassing, simple past and past participle debarrassed)

entries.meaning: (dated, transitive) To disembarrass, disentangle, or free from.
examples: Miss Gryce snored at last:  […]  I was debarrassed of interruption; my half-effaced thought instantly revived.
